{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8f1814ea-4038-407f-86b1-65048d1f48e4","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine, but I can still walk you through **how to identify the runtime and configure dumps**. Here's the playbook:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Determine CoreCLR vs NativeAOT\n\nRun these checks against your actual PID:\n\n```bash\n# Check if the process loaded libcoreclr.so (CoreCLR indicator)\ncat /proc/<PID>/maps | grep -q libcoreclr && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"Likely NativeAOT\"\n\n# Double-check: NativeAOT binaries are fully self-contained ELFs\nfile /proc/<PID>/exe\n# NativeAOT → \"ELF ... statically linked\" or no libcoreclr dependency\n# CoreCLR  → dynamically linked, loads libcoreclr.so\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Configure Crash Dumps\n\n#### For **CoreCLR** apps:\n\nSet these environment variables before launching:\n\n```bash\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1          # Enable dump on crash\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4            # 4 = Full heap dump (1=Mini, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t   # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n```\n\n#### For **NativeAOT** apps:\n\nNativeAOT doesn't use the CoreCLR dump infrastructure. Use the **kernel core dump** mechanism instead:\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# Configure dump path via kernel\necho '/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\n# Or use systemd-coredump (if using systemd)\n# Dumps land in /var/lib/systemd/coredump/ automatically\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Verify the Setup\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n\n# For CoreCLR: send SIGABRT to test\nkill -6 <PID>\n\n# Check dump was written\nls -lh /tmp/dumps/\n```\n\n**Key difference**: CoreCLR dumps are analyzed with `dotnet-dump analyze`, while NativeAOT core dumps are analyzed with `lldb` or `gdb` (since there's no managed runtime to introspect).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c91f3186-6733-43c4-9994-53c479709767","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"6012:2E8AE9:E26AE8:1068D5D:69EACC16"},"id":"47f73b21-c5b6-4e42-9f21-90d6e04b687e","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:49:25.982Z","parentId":"beb4e98b-05a6-46d1-a236-ddf2f4e3cae0"}
